9081  if ((flags & (JS_PROP_HAS_WRITABLE | JS_PROP_WRITABLE)) == JS_PROP_HAS_WRITABLE) {
9082  JSValue val1;
9083  if (js_shape_prepare_update(ctx, p, &prs))
9084  return -1;
9085  val1 = JS_DupValue(ctx, *pr->u.var_ref->pvalue);
9086  free_var_ref(ctx->rt, pr->u.var_ref);
9087  pr->u.value = val1;
9088  prs->flags &= ~(JS_PROP_TMASK | JS_PROP_WRITABLE);
9089  }
9090  } else if ((prs->flags & JS_PROP_TMASK) == JS_PROP_AUTOINIT) {
9091  /* XXX: should never happen, type was reset above */
9092  abort();
9093  } else {
9094  if (flags & JS_PROP_HAS_VALUE) {
9095  JS_FreeValue(ctx, pr->u.value);
9096  pr->u.value = JS_DupValue(ctx, val);
9097  }
9098  if (flags & JS_PROP_HAS_WRITABLE) {
9099  if (js_update_property_flags(ctx, p, &prs,
9100  (prs->flags & ~JS_PROP_WRITABLE) |
9101  (flags & JS_PROP_WRITABLE)))
9102  return -1;
9103  }
9104  }
9105  }
9106  }
9107  mask = 0;
9108  if (flags & JS_PROP_HAS_CONFIGURABLE)
9109  mask |= JS_PROP_CONFIGURABLE;
9110  if (flags & JS_PROP_HAS_ENUMERABLE)
9111  mask |= JS_PROP_ENUMERABLE;
9112  if (js_update_property_flags(ctx, p, &prs,
9113  (prs->flags & ~mask) | (flags & mask)))
9114  return -1;
9115  return TRUE;
9116  }
9117 
9118  /* handle modification of fast array elements */
9119  if (p->fast_array) {
9120  uint32_t idx;
9121  uint32_t prop_flags;
9122  if (p->class_id == JS_CLASS_ARRAY) {
9123  if (__JS_AtomIsTaggedInt(prop)) {
9124  idx = __JS_AtomToUInt32(prop);
9125  if (idx < p->u.array.count) {
9126  prop_flags = get_prop_flags(flags, JS_PROP_C_W_E);
9127  if (prop_flags != JS_PROP_C_W_E)
9128  goto convert_to_slow_array;
9129  if (flags & (JS_PROP_HAS_GET | JS_PROP_HAS_SET)) {
9130  convert_to_slow_array:
9131  if (convert_fast_array_to_array(ctx, p))
9132  return -1;
9133  else
9134  goto redo_prop_update;
9135  }
9136  if (flags & JS_PROP_HAS_VALUE) {
9137  set_value(ctx, &p->u.array.u.values[idx], JS_DupValue(ctx, val));
9138  }
9139  return TRUE;
9140  }
9141  }
9142  } else if (p->class_id >= JS_CLASS_UINT8C_ARRAY &&
9143  p->class_id <= JS_CLASS_FLOAT64_ARRAY) {
9144  JSValue num;
9145  int ret;
9146 
9147  if (!__JS_AtomIsTaggedInt(prop)) {
9148  /* slow path with to handle all numeric indexes */
9149  num = JS_AtomIsNumericIndex1(ctx, prop);
9150  if (JS_IsUndefined(num))
9151  goto typed_array_done;
9152  if (JS_IsException(num))
9153  return -1;
9154  ret = JS_NumberIsInteger(ctx, num);
9155  if (ret < 0) {
9156  JS_FreeValue(ctx, num);
9157  return -1;
9158  }
9159  if (!ret) {
9160  JS_FreeValue(ctx, num);
9161  return JS_ThrowTypeErrorOrFalse(ctx, flags, "non integer index in typed array");
9162  }
9163  ret = JS_NumberIsNegativeOrMinusZero(ctx, num);
9164  JS_FreeValue(ctx, num);
9165  if (ret) {
9166  return JS_ThrowTypeErrorOrFalse(ctx, flags, "negative index in typed array");
9167  }
9168  if (!__JS_AtomIsTaggedInt(prop))
9169  goto typed_array_oob;
9170  }
9171  idx = __JS_AtomToUInt32(prop);
9172  /* if the typed array is detached, p->u.array.count = 0 */
9173  if (idx >= typed_array_get_length(ctx, p)) {
9174  typed_array_oob:
9175  return JS_ThrowTypeErrorOrFalse(ctx, flags, "out-of-bound index in typed array");
9176  }
9177  prop_flags = get_prop_flags(flags, JS_PROP_ENUMERABLE | JS_PROP_WRITABLE);
9178  if (flags & (JS_PROP_HAS_GET | JS_PROP_HAS_SET) ||
9179  prop_flags != (JS_PROP_ENUMERABLE | JS_PROP_WRITABLE)) {
9180  return JS_ThrowTypeErrorOrFalse(ctx, flags, "invalid descriptor flags");
9181  }
9182  if (flags & JS_PROP_HAS_VALUE) {
9183  return JS_SetPropertyValue(ctx, this_obj, JS_NewInt32(ctx, idx), JS_DupValue(ctx, val), flags);
9184  }
9185  return TRUE;
9186  typed_array_done: ;
9187  }
9188  }
9189 
9190  return JS_CreateProperty(ctx, p, prop, val, getter, setter, flags);
9191 }
